						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Sati stone on the bund of Saṇṇakeṟe.</hi></p>						

						<p>A.D. 1404.</p>						

						<p>This inscription dated in <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1326, Tāraṇa, Chaitra s11u. [5], Sunday,</hi> states that <hi rend="bold">Māde-Nāyaka</hi> installed the <hi rend="italic">mahāsati</hi> slab in memory of his mother <hi rend="bold">Malidēvi</hi> who died by the rite of <hi rend="italic">samādhi</hi> on account of the death of her husband (name lost).</p>						

						<p>The details of the date correspond to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1404, March 16, Sunday.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
